&lt;p&gt;Are you enthusiastic about ensuring positive outcomes for children and families? Do you have knowledge and experience of the delivery of the Healthy Child Programme?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have a vacancy for a Community Nursery Nurse based in Hillingdon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supporting the Children&#39;s Universal Health Service 0-19 teams in the delivery of the Healthy Child Programme to children aged 0 – 5 years and their families. We are looking for an enthusiastic practitioner, preferably with experience of working with families experiencing a wide range of health and social needs. Experience in behaviour management, parenting advice and breastfeeding is desirable as is an understanding of child development, safeguarding and working with vulnerable families. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for a flexible, motivated and enthusiastic individual who can communicate effectively, and are able to work independently as well as part of a team. Travel across bases within Hillingdon is expected, therefore the ability to drive and have access to a car for work purposes will be expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
